1. Project Overview

The CONA Email Workflow is an existing production workflow used for processing incoming email related work items. The workflow interacts with a CNB Web Service to retrieve account related information from the database and populate workflow properties during processing.

The business requested an enhancement to capture and display Division information associated with an account. This information will be retrieved from the database and made available within the workflow so that users can view and update the value during the workflow processing stages.

This document describes the design changes implemented across the workflow, web service, database, and BPF configuration in order to support this requirement.

2. Business Requirement

The business requested the ability to capture Division information for each account processed through the CONA Email Workflow.

The key requirements are listed below.

Introduce a new workflow property named Division.

Retrieve the Division information from the database through the existing CNB Web Service.

Make the Division property available in all user interaction workflow queues.

Allow users to view and update the Division property during workflow processing.

Allow users to search workflow items using the Division property in the BPF queue filters.

Display the Division property in the workflow queue result sets.

3. Existing System Behavior

Currently the workflow retrieves account information through the CNB Web Service. The web service executes a database query against the Deposit table and returns several account related attributes.

The returned values are assigned to corresponding workflow properties and displayed within the workflow steps.

The existing implementation does not include any attribute related to Division. The Deposit table does not store division information.

4. High Level Solution

To support the Division property requirement, the following design changes were implemented.

A new database table containing cost center to division mapping was created by the business.

A database view was created to merge the existing Deposit table and the new CostCenterDivision table.

The CNB Web Service query was modified to retrieve data from the new view instead of directly querying the Deposit table.

A new workflow property named Division was added to the workflow definition.

The Division property was enabled in all user interaction workflow queues.

BPF configuration was updated to allow filtering and displaying Division information in the queue user interface.

5. Database Changes

The business introduced a new database table named CostCenterDivision. This table stores mapping information between cost center numbers and division names.

Since the existing web service query retrieves information from the Deposit table, a database view was created to combine information from both tables.

The view merges Deposit account information with division data using the cost center number as the join condition.

View Name

deposit_CostCenterDivision_View

Database

ACCT_CLIENT

Purpose of the view

The view provides a single dataset containing:

Account information from the Deposit table

Division information from the CostCenterDivision table

This allows the web service to retrieve all required attributes through a single query.

6. Database View Definition

The following view was created in the ACCT_CLIENT database.

USE [ACCT_CLIENT]
GO

SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO

SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO

CREATE VIEW [dbo].[deposit_CostCenterDivision_View]
AS

SELECT
    d.Account_Number AS AccountNumber,
    d.Account_branch_cbc_number AS BranchNumber,
    d.Account_charge_center_number AS CostCenter,
    RTRIM(d.Account_name) AS EntityName,
    d.Account_primary_customer_number AS CISNumber,
    d.Account_type_code AS AccountTypeCode,

    (SELECT RIGHT('00000'+CAST(Account_Secondary_Officer_Num AS varchar(5)),5)
     FROM FT_Deposit
     WHERE ACCOUNT_NUMBER = d.Account_Number) AS OfficerNumber,

    d.Account_taxpayer_id_number AS TaxIDNumber,

    CASE(d.Account_charge_center_number)
        WHEN 660 THEN 'e'
        WHEN 665 THEN 'e'
        WHEN 667 THEN 'e'
        WHEN 668 THEN 'e'
        WHEN 669 THEN 'e'
        WHEN 682 THEN 'e'
    END AS DeptIndicator,

    c.Division_Name AS DivisionName

FROM Deposit d
INNER JOIN CostCenterDivision c
ON d.Account_charge_center_number = c.Cost_Center
7. CNB Web Service Changes

The CNB Web Service configuration was modified in order to retrieve the Division value from the new database view.

Configuration File

kwikwork_kwikworkbpf.xml

Location

W:\www\CNBWebService

The previous query in the configuration file queried the Deposit table directly. That query was commented out and replaced with a new query referencing the database view.

Previous implementation

The earlier query retrieved account attributes from the Deposit table only.

New implementation

The query now retrieves data from the database view:

ACCT_CLIENT.dbo.deposit_CostCenterDivision_View

The updated query now returns an additional column:

DivisionName

The AccountNumber parameter is passed to the query and used to retrieve the corresponding record from the view.

8. Workflow Changes

The workflow definition file was updated to include the new property.

Workflow File

CONAEmailCaptureWorkflow.pep

New Workflow Property

Division

Property Type

String

Property Access

Read / Write

The workflow now assigns the Division value returned from the web service to the workflow property during processing.

9. Workflow Step Configuration

The Division property was added to the following workflow queues.

CONAEmail_FirstLook
CONAEmail_DataEntry
CONAEmail_Supervisor

The property was configured with Read and Write access in these steps so that users can view and modify the value if required.

10. BPF Configuration Changes

The workflow queues are managed using the BPF interface.

Configuration file modified

Web.config

Location

W:\web-kwikworkbpf\www\Config

The following updates were made.

Queue Filter Enhancement

The Division property was added as a searchable field in the queue filter panel. Users can now search workflow items using Division as a search parameter.

Queue Result Set Enhancement

The Division column was added to the queue result set display so that users can view the Division value directly from the queue listing.

Workflow Work Item View

The Division property is now visible in the workflow form when a user opens a work item. The property is configured as read/write in the user interaction steps.

11. Components Modified

Database

New database view created to merge deposit and cost center division data.

Web Service

Query updated to retrieve data from the new database view.

Workflow

New workflow property added and mapped to the web service response.

Workflow Queues

Division property enabled in user interaction queues.

BPF Configuration

Queue filters and result sets updated to include Division.

12. Deployment Document

The deployment must be executed in the following order.

1 Database changes
2 Web service configuration changes
3 Workflow deployment
4 BPF configuration update

